cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with abstract syntax and semantics, which are closely related to logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses modules and linearity, which are important concepts in programming languages. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with modularity and merging of syntax, which are relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the definition of arity and signature, which are important concepts in formal languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the construction of amalgamated sums, which are related to data structures.
